The Mayflower
From the wharf of the bay,  
   Rise, sailor, remove—  
The bright ship for its journey  
   Of hope and of love;  
And at the gates of dawn  
   Shall the morning glow—  
On the burning sea  
   In the chill, we shall go.

---

- Oliver Wendell Holmes Sr
